Demo for greedy DPP sampling¶

Import dependencies. (synthetic_datasets is a custom Python script that for generating noisy samples from Swiss Roll and S-curve sklearn datasets).

In [1]:
from importlib import reload
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import Axes3D
import numpy as np
import seaborn as sns

import synthetic_datasets

Swiss Roll¶

Generate Swiss roll synthetic data

In [2]:
reload(synthetic_datasets)
sr = synthetic_datasets.SwissRoll(200)
sr.sample(5000, gamma_shape=1.0)

Visualize sampled points¶

3D plot¶

In [3]:
fig = plt.figure()
ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')
ax.scatter(sr.full_coordinates[:,0], 
           sr.full_coordinates[:,1], 
           sr.full_coordinates[:,2],
          c=sr.full_t, cmap="jet", alpha=0.05)

ax.scatter(sr.centers[:,0], 
           sr.centers[:,1], 
           sr.centers[:,2],
          c="k", cmap="jet", marker="o")

ax.view_init(10,80)

Distribution of metacell variances¶

Synthetic data adds isotropic Gaussian noise to each point sampled from Swiss Roll. Noise is drawn from Gamma distribution and is different for each point.

In [5]:
sns.distplot(sr.variances)
plt.title("Swiss roll\nDistribution of variances")
Out[5]:
Text(0.5, 1.0, 'Swiss roll\nDistribution of variances')

Metacells¶

In [7]:
import SparseDPP

Model initialization¶

Uses Jaccard similarity.

In [62]:
reload(SparseDPP)

# jaccard kernel kNN neighbors
n_neighbors = 15

sr_dpp = SparseDPP.dpp(sr.full_coordinates, verbose=True)
sr_dpp.initialize_kernel(n_neighbors)

Computing kNN graph...
Making graph symmetric...
Computing intersections...
Computing Jaccard similarity for 291178 pairs...

Sampling¶

Below does greedy sampling without constraints. Adds one new metacell per iteration. You can add a parameter for max number of iterations (and hence max number of meta-cells) as follows:

max_iter = 100
idx = sr_dpp.sample(max_iter)
In [63]:
idx = sr_dpp.sample()

Visualization¶

3D projection¶

Show metacells on 3D plot.

In [84]:
fig = plt.figure()
ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')
ax.scatter(sr.full_coordinates[:,0], 
           sr.full_coordinates[:,1], 
           sr.full_coordinates[:,2],
          c=sr.full_t, cmap="jet", alpha=0.05,
          label="og data")


ax.scatter(sr.centers[:,0], 
           sr.centers[:,1], 
           sr.centers[:,2],
          c=sr.t, cmap="jet")

ax.scatter(sr_metacells[:,0], 
           sr_metacells[:,1], 
           sr_metacells[:,2],
          c="k", marker="x",
          label="metacell center")

ax.view_init(10,80)
ax.legend()

<matplotlib.legend.Legend at 0x1350a6550>

Unrolled Swiss roll¶

In [86]:
fig = plt.figure()
ax = fig.add_subplot(111)

ax.scatter(sr.t, 
           sr.centers[:,1], 
          c=sr.t, cmap="jet", label="original center",
          s=sr.sizes**2/20, alpha=0.3)

# plot metacells
ax.scatter(sr_metacells_t, 
           sr_metacells[:,1], 
          c="k", marker="x", label="metacell",
          s=sr_dpp.get_metacell_sizes()**2/50)

ax.legend(loc="upper left")
Out[86]:
<matplotlib.legend.Legend at 0x138543080>
